                                <div class="card-p ">
                            <p>Paint is used to protect all sorts of buildings and structures from the effects of water and sun. Wooden buildings such as houses are usually painted because a coat of paint prevents water seeping into the wood and making it rot. The paint also helps to prevent the wood from drying out in the hot sun.</p>

                            <p>Incredibly, some forms of paint can actually reduce the danger of a fire spreading in your house. Fire resistant paints, also known as intumescent coatings, are a passive fire protection measure that are well worth the investment. Obviously these products aren&rsquo;t going to save your home from a fire, but they can form an important part of your fire safety measures in the house.</p>

                                </div>
                            </div>
